  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">L. P. Ashmead writes: &quot;Howland &amp; Preston were with me during their Easter vacation.&quot; He tells of the afflictions suffered by his sister Dolly. L. P. Ashmead says that &quot;the monument for my dear wife at St. James the Less is about finished.&quot; He would like Deborah Weston to suggest an inscription. His recollection of his old home in New Bedford is &quot;tempered with sadness.&quot; He refers to Joseph Ricketson and other people in New Bedford. L. P. Ashmead is staying with his brother John and his mother.</subfield>
